==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anent
<hw>A*nent"</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>prep.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>anent</ets>,
<ets>anentis</ets>, <ets>anence</ets>, <ets>anens</ets>,
<ets>anents</ets>, AS. <ets>onefen</ets>, <ets>onemn</ets>;
<ets>an</ets>, <ets>on</ets>, on + <ets>efen</ets> even, equal; hence
meaning, on an equality with, even with, beside. See <er>Even</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <mark>[Scot. & Prov. Eng.]</mark> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Over against; <as>as, he lives <ex>anent</ex> the
church</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>About; concerning; in respect; <as>as, he said
nothing <ex>anent</ex> this particular</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anenterous</ent>⟦br⟧
